docs.lead_paragraph: Based on the local market quotations for the French franc last week, the dollar was strong. The highest was 71.69 cents, reached on Saturday, following a sharp break in all gold currencies of the Continent, as a result of which the franc sold down to 5.46 1/2 cents. The week's lowest was 68.85, on Wednesday, and the close 71.04, a gain of .77 over the preceding Saturday.

docs.lead_paragraph: Gold shipped abroad in September was smaller in amount than in either of the two preceding months and was consigned, as in those months, principally to France.
